# Azure Static Website Hosting Lab

## 📌 Overview

In this project, I deployed a serverless static website using Azure Blob Storage. Instead of managing servers, I used Azure's built-in static website hosting feature to publish a live site to the internet.

## 🚀 Technologies Used

* Microsoft Azure
* Azure Storage Account
* Azure Blob Storage ($web container)
* HTML

## 🏗️ Architecture

User → Azure Static Website Endpoint → Azure Storage Account ($web container) → index.html

## ⚙️ Steps Performed

### 1. Created Resource Group

* Name: rg-lab01-dylanbryson1
* Region: East US

### 2. Created Storage Account

* Name: stlab01dylanbryson1
* Performance: Standard
* Redundancy: Locally Redundant Storage (LRS)

### 3. Enabled Static Website Hosting

* Enabled static website feature
* Configured index document: index.html
* Azure generated a public endpoint URL

### 4. Created and Uploaded Website

* Built a simple HTML page
* Uploaded it to the $web container

### 5. Validated Deployment

* Accessed the site using the public endpoint
* Confirmed successful deployment

## 🌐 Live Demo

https://stlab01dylanbryson.z13.web.core.windows.net/



## 🧠 Key Takeaways

* Learned how to host a static website in Azure without servers
* Understood Blob Storage static website hosting
* Practiced deploying and validating cloud resources
* Gained experience with public endpoints

## 🧹 Cleanup

Deleted the resource group to avoid unnecessary costs


